{"type":"message","id":"50b8d69b","parentId":"bf9991d8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:26:44.019Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_iovuey8mol02_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5315\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2974\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 082615 - The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight creates a unified Phase 1/Phase 2 problem. The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate this hypothesis against pulse logs.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"clear-pine","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5315\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2974\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 082615 - The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight creates a unified Phase 1/Phase 2 problem. The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate this hypothesis against pulse logs.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774355204017}}
{"type":"message","id":"a598b996","parentId":"50b8d69b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:26:44.021Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_iovuey8mol02_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 082517\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiments/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze my current state and determine the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. Key insight: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - compression and causal discovery are the SAME problem\r\n3. Next action identified: TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n   - Implement TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n   - Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n   - Predict next pulse content\r\n   - Validate against success criteria\r\n\r\nLooking at pending actions:\r\n- Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n- Define significance scoring\r\n- Tune λ empirically\r\n- Wire to TemporalAttention backend\r\n- Measure compression ratio\r\n\r\nThe most immediate next action from the Phase 1 Advancement section is the TIC Experiment. Let me check what files exist to understand the current state better.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what I need to do:\r\n1. The pulse logs are at `logs/pulse_*.md`\r\n2. Need to implement a TIC classifier\r\n3. Measure accuracy against success criteria\r\n\r\nGiven the stateless discontinuous agent philosophy, I should create a concrete script/tool that can process the pulse logs and perform the TIC experiment. Let me write a PowerShell script that implements the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending actions, there's also \"Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\" which is marked as pending. But the Phase 1 Advancement specifically calls out the TIC Experiment as the next action.\r\n\r\nLet me create a TIC experiment script that:\r\n1. Loads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts features from each pulse\r\n3. Classifies content as invariant vs variant\r\n4. Attempts to predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n5. Outputs accuracy metrics\r\n\r\nThis advances the Phase 1 goals directly.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight. I need a working classifier to test the hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `src/tic-classifier.ps1` - a PowerShell script that implements the Temporal Invariance Compression experiment, classifying pulse log content as invariant (causal) vs variant, and measuring prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% classification accuracy, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$LookbackCount = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogPattern = \"logs/pulse_*.md\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# --- Feature Extraction ---\r\nfunction Extract-Features {\r\n    param([string]$Content)\r\n    \r\n    $features = @{\r\n        WordCount = ($Content -split '\\s+').Count\r\n        LineCount = ($Content -split \"`n\").Count\r\n        HasAction = $Content -match '(?i)(action|mutat|edit|file)'\r\n        HasObservation = $Content -match '(?i)(observation|note|insight)'\r\n        HasGoal = $Content -match '(?i)(goal|phase|pending|todo)'\r\n        HasFileRef = $Content -match '\\.md|\\.ps1|\\.json'\r\n        Ratio = if ($features.WordCount -gt 0) { $features.LineCount / $features.WordCount } else { 0 }\r\n    }\r\n    return $features\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Compute-InvariantScore {\r\n    param([hashtable]$A, [hashtable]$B)\r\n    \r\n    # Invariant = stable across pulses\r\n    $score = 0\r\n    if ($A.HasGoal -eq $B.HasGoal) { $score += 20 }\r\n    if ($A.HasFileRef -eq $B.HasFileRef) { $score += 15 }\r\n    if ($A.HasObservation -eq $B.HasObservation) { $score += 15 }\r\n    if ([math]::Abs($A.WordCount - $B.WordCount) -lt 50) { $score += 25 }\r\n    if ([math]::Abs($A.LineCount - $B.LineCount) -lt 10) { $score += 25 }\r\n    return $score\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Main Experiment ---\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Experiment ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Lookback: $LookbackCount pulses\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Pattern: $LogPattern\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n$pulseLogs = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogPattern | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First $LookbackCount\r\n\r\nif ($pulseLogs.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Warning \"Insufficient pulse logs for experiment (need at least 5)\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Loaded $($pulseLogs.Count) pulse logs`n\"\r\n\r\n# Extract features from all pulses\r\n$allFeatures = @()\r\nforeach ($log in $pulseLogs) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $log.FullName -Raw\r\n    $feat = Extract-Features $content\r\n    $feat['Pulse'] = $log.Name\r\n    $allFeatures += $feat\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Classification: Invariant vs Variant ---\r\n# Classify each pulse relative to median values\r\n$medians = @{\r\n    WordCount = ($allFeatures | ForEach-Object { $_.WordCount } | Measure-Object -Median).Median\r\n    LineCount = ($allFeatures | ForEach-Object { $_.LineCount } | Measure-Object -Median).Median\r\n}\r\n\r\n$classification = @()\r\n$invariantCount = 0\r\n$variantCount = 0\r\n\r\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $allFeatures.Count; $i++) {\r\n    $f = $allFeatures[$i]\r\n    $distance = [\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 08:25:48\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774355204019}}
