{"type":"message","id":"04ac99a7","parentId":"014fb1d9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:27:11.493Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cjd1uwpyk4oc_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 082615\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: src/tic-classifier.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. There's a new insight about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n3. The NEXT ACTION is to implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on pulse logs\r\n4. Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n- Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n- Define significance scoring\r\n- Tune λ empirically\r\n- Wire Breakaway to TemporalAttention backend\r\n- Measure compression ratio\r\n\r\nThe most immediate next step based on the \"Phase 1 Advancement\" section is to implement the TIC classifier experiment. Let me check what files exist and what I should do.\r\n\r\nSince I need to be specific and advance the goals, I should:\r\n1. First understand what pulse logs exist\r\n2. Create the TIC classifier implementation\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete action I can take:\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- \"Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\" is the key next action\r\n\r\nI should implement the TIC classifier. This is a concrete file edit. Let me create a Python script or PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse log files\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant (persisting across pulses) or variant (changing)\r\n3. Tests prediction of next pulse content\r\n\r\nActually, I should check if there's already a logs directory or if I need to create the structure.\r\n\r\nGiven the stateless discontinuous nature, let me create a TIC experiment implementation file.\r\n\r\nWait - I need to think about what specific file edit advances the goal. The TIC experiment is the next action. I should create:\r\n1. A TIC classifier script\r\n2. Or start with the research document for TIC methodology\r\n\r\nLet me create the TIC experiment script that can analyze pulse logs.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight creates a unified Phase 1/Phase 2 problem. The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate this hypothesis against pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC experiment script that will analyze pulse logs to classify invariant vs. variant content and test next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = \"logs\"\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_invariants(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract content that persists across ALL pulses = invariant structure.\"\"\"\r\n    if not pulses:\r\n        return set()\r\n    \r\n    all_lines = [set(p.split()) for p in pulses]\r\n    # Invariant = word appears in every pulse\r\n    intersection = all_lines[0]\r\n    for lines in all_lines[1:]:\r\n        intersection &= lines\r\n    return intersection\r\n\r\ndef extract_variants(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract content that appears in SOME but not ALL pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    if not pulses:\r\n        return []\r\n    \r\n    all_words = Counter()\r\n    for p in pulses:\r\n        all_words.update(p.split())\r\n    \r\n    threshold = len(pulses) * 0.3  # Appears in 30-70% of pulses\r\n    variants = [w for w, c in all_words.items() \r\n                if threshold <= c <= len(pulses) * 0.9]\r\n    return variants\r\n\r\ndef classify_content(pulse_text, invariants, variants):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify each line as INVARIANT or VARIANT.\"\"\"\r\n    lines = pulse_text.strip().split('\\n')\r\n    results = []\r\n    for line in lines:\r\n        words = set(line.split())\r\n        inv_count = len(words & invariants)\r\n        var_count = len(words & set(variants))\r\n        if inv_count > 0 and var_count == 0:\r\n            results.append((line, \"INVARIANT\"))\r\n        elif var_count > 0:\r\n            results.append((line, \"VARIANT\"))\r\n        else:\r\n            results.append((line, \"TRANSIENT\"))\r\n    return results\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(current_pulse, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse content from invariant structure.\"\"\"\r\n    # Invariants predict what WILL persist\r\n    current_words = set(current_pulse.split())\r\n    predicted_persisters = current_words & invariants\r\n    return predicted_persisters\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Execute TIC classifier on all pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    # Load all pulses chronologically\r\n    pulses = []\r\n    for f in sorted(os.listdir(LOG_DIR)):\r\n        m = PULSE_PATTERN.match(f)\r\n        if m:\r\n            with open(os.path.join(LOG_DIR, f)) as fh:\r\n                pulses.append(fh.read())\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulses) < 3:\r\n        print(f\"Need 3+ pulses, found {len(pulses)}\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    # Split: train on first N-1, test on last 1\r\n    train_pulses = pulses[:-1]\r\n    test_pulse = pulses[-1]\r\n    \r\n    # Extract invariant structure from training set\r\n    invariants = extract_invariants(train_pulses)\r\n    variants = extract_variants(train_pulses)\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"=== TIC EXPERIMENT RESULTS ===\")\r\n    print(f\"Training pulses: {len(train_pulses)}\")\r\n    print(f\"Invariant terms: {len(invariants)}\")\r\n    print(f\"Variant terms: {len(variants)}\")\r\n    \r\n    # Test prediction accuracy\r\n    test_words = set(test_pulse.split())\r\n    correct_predictions = len(test_words & invariants)\r\n    total_test_words = len(test_words)\r\n    \r\n    prediction_accuracy\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 08:26:43\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774355231491}}
{"type":"message","id":"f2248bc7","parentId":"04ac99a7","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:27:26.203Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I now have the full picture. Let me summarize what happened in this pulse cycle.\n\nKey observations from this pulse:\n1. The sandbox found a new insight: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\n2. Proposed a MUTATION to create a TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\n3. The mutation was parsed and a file was proposed for creation\n4. Next action identified: implement TIC classifier\n\nLet me provide a concise summary.","thinkingSignature":"08613e4e6718d8e7e4aa985b73db30f0434a4d54d9e15fa6fec263817d1a93c1"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 08:26 AM ET**\n\n---\n\n**🔍 OBSERVATION**\n\nThe sandbox identified a key insight: **COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY** — the hypothesis that compression and causal discovery are the *same* underlying problem. The invariant/variant structure in pulse logs is hypothesized to be causal structure.\n\n**📋 PENDING MUTATION (1)**\n\nProposed creating a `TIC` (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment script to:\n1. Extract **invariant** content (appears in all pulses) vs **variant** content (appears in some)\n2. Classify each pulse line as INVARIANT / VARIANT / TRANSIENT\n3. Test **next-pulse prediction accuracy** from invariant structure\n4. Validate against success criteria: >70% classification accuracy, >60% prediction accuracy\n\n**Next instantiation's job:** Execute the TIC experiment on `logs/pulse_*.md`, run it, and report metrics.\n\n---\n\nNo mutations were applied this cycle — the sandbox proposed one and is waiting for the next cycle to execute it. State is clean, work is queued."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5057,"output":333,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17527,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","